$interpreted: Clark: Mr. Sherlock...I-I got it.
Sherlock: Hmph, that dirty old fart thinks he can snatch that deal from up under my nose, then sell it back to me at a ridiculous rate...
Sherlock: Luckily, I've got my ways.
Sherlock: Excellent. My joints have been a mess recently, finally get to change 'em!
Clark: Uh...aren't they for Maria?
Sherlock: What!? I can't change my joints, is that it!? If I'm gonna fix her, you know how many parts I'm gonna use!?
Clark: I-I-I understand...I'm sorry.
Sherlock: Next...let's see...go get me the red thorn of a cactus.
Clark: Red thorn from a cactus?
Sherlock: It's a very tough material, the more you get the better.
Clark: ...Sounds tiring.
Sherlock: I tell you to go, you go! No use in useless blibber-blabber!
Clark: Redthorn Cactus...this should be it.
Ned: Hey! You can't just take that out!
Ned: You can't take the thorns out of cacti from around here, don't you know that!?
Clark: B-But, your father told me to...
Ned: Aigh, Father's always acting like this...he didn't tell you, did he? There's a special way you gotta do it.
Clark: Huh? Sherlock didn't mention that.
Ned: Before you pull it out, you've got to talk about how great they are.
Ned: Miss Cactus, you've got such rosy cheeks today. I've never seen a cactus as beautiful as you.
Ned: Really! Just look at those brilliant flowers on your head, and these thorns, my goodness! They're sharper than a rose's——
Clark: Hey, you've got to switch up your expression! Com' on! Put some feeling into it!
Ned: It's unbelievable, I must say. How is it possible that there exists a plant as beautiful as you?
Clark: Nothing too bizarre for the desert...
Ned: It's such a privilege to meet such a beautiful cactus today.
Ned: Darn, the sun's about to set. Best come back tomorrow.
Clark: The cactus understands human language?
Ned: Not exactly. More like something us hunters of the desert have picked up.
Clark: In any case, thank you. I hope Mr. Sherlock actually starts repairing Maria this time...
Ned: I saw that Father has been making you run around collecting stuff these past few days. He hasn't started fixing your friend yet?
Clark: I don't know. When does he plan on starting...?
Ned: I see...I know who to go to!
Clark: Who?
Ned: A goddess...the only one on this earth who's able to convince Sherlock of anything!
Sherlock: Honey, come and visit your father, won't you!?
Lisa: Dad, you never come to my new home to visit Ned and I. Guess I'll have to come to you again.
Sherlock: Who told you to get married anyway! Hmph.
Lisa: Dad, what is this thing!
Sherlock: It's just like your father; it's a robot.
Lisa: She's sooo cute. Wah, so pretty~ Dad, give it to me!
Sherlock: Give it to you!? No, no, no, no, no, no...
Sherlock: One look at her structure and I can tell she's dangerous!
Lisa: So what? ~ I want her to be my friend~
Lisa: Dadddd, hurry up and fix her~ Just fix her up so she's not dangerous, okay!?
Lisa: I wanna talk with her~
Sherlock: B-But, she's...she's severely damaged...
Lisa: Ohhh come off it~ Dad, you're so smart, you can fix her in no time!
Sherlock: W-Well, of course...
Sherlock: Whatta you think, your dad can only fix useless crap!?
Lisa: Yay! My dad's the smartest one in town, and he loves me sooo much!
Sherlock: But to fix her I need so many parts...
Sherlock: That useless flesh bag!
Sherlock: Geez! Tell him to get stuff and he's just loafing around, like a loaf of bread! Who knows where he went off to!
Lisa: Hehe, the deed is done.
